{"lemma":"زُبْيَة","slug":"زُبْيَة","root":"ز.ب.#","root_slug":"ز-ب-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ب-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17463"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17463","headword_ar":"زُبْيَةٌ","root":"zbY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an elevated piece of ground, which the water does not overflow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rubFY","text_ar":"رُبًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) Hence, (TA,) it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaga Als~ayolu Alz~ubaY","text_ar":"بَلَغَ السَّيْلُ الزُّبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The torrent reached"},{"kind":"text","text":"the tops of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hills which they do not usually overflow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~ubaY","text_ar":"الزُّبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~uboyapu","text_ar":"الزُّبْيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense next following: [but the meaning is virtually the same:] (Meyd:) the prov. is applied to a thing, or an affair, or a case, exceeding the ordinary bounds or limit. (Meyd, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pitfall for a lion"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or a wolf"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dug in a high place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb,) for which reason it is thus called: (S:) pl. as above. (Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hollow dug in the ground, in which a sportsman conceals himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the objects of the chase"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hollow dug in the ground, in which one roasts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broils, for himself, and bakes bread."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so where it is said in a trad. of an Arab of the desert,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarad~aY fiY zuboyapK","text_ar":"تَرَدَّى فِى زُبْيَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fell into a well"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b6-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excavation made by ants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which they make not save in a high place. (TA.) ―         -b7-  Some include this word among those that have contr. significations. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Meyd","Mgh","Msb"]}]}}